CONTEXT
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
After Task 4.2 rewrote the RMS intent classifier, selected_collection
in state holds values like "rms_timesheet" and "rms_projectplan"
(lowercase with prefix). But the three agent nodes
(creator_agent_node, reviewer_agent_node, approver_agent_node)
still have legacy condition `if selected_collection == "RMS":` at
the top of their LLM-binding logic.

This condition is now ALWAYS false. Execution falls into the
`else:` branch which sets `full_text = ""` and returns silently.
Empty stream to user.

This task changes the condition to match the new classifier output
and adds diagnostic prints to make the next round of testing easier.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
SCOPE
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

In app/workflows/rms_workflow/nodes.py:

In EACH of these three functions: creator_agent_node,
reviewer_agent_node, approver_agent_node:

Find the line that says:
    if selected_collection == "RMS":

Change it to:
    if selected_collection and selected_collection.lower().startswith("rms_"):

This makes the condition true for "rms_timesheet" and "rms_projectplan"
(the values the new classifier produces).

Also in each of the three agent node functions, add this print
statement immediately after the function signature / docstring,
BEFORE any other logic:

    print(
        f"[DIAG-RMS] <function_name> entered. "
        f"emp_no={state.get('emp_no')}, "
        f"selected_collection={state.get('selected_collection')!r}, "
        f"selected_agent_role={state.get('selected_agent_role')!r}, "
        f"will_enter_rms_branch={bool(state.get('selected_collection', '').lower().startswith('rms_'))}",
        flush=True
    )

Replace <function_name> with the actual function name (e.g.,
creator_agent_node, reviewer_agent_node, approver_agent_node).

If approver_agent_node already has a print at the top (from
previous diagnostic), REPLACE that print with this new more
informative one. Do NOT keep two prints.

Do NOT add any other changes. Do NOT modify branch internals.
Do NOT touch the `else:` branch.

